G&lt;U+00E9&gt;rard Paul Alain Feldzer (born 10 February 1944) is a consultant and aeronautical popularizer. He is a former French airline pilot, President of Comit&lt;U+00E9&gt; r&lt;U+00E9&gt;gional de tourisme d'&lt;U+00CE&gt;le-de-France (Regional Committee of &lt;U+00CE&gt;le-de-France Tourism) since May 2010,1 and Vice-Pr&lt;U+00E9&gt;sident of Ports de Paris (Ports of Paris).
He has also been Regional Advisor of &lt;U+00CE&gt;le-de-France for Europe &lt;U+00C9&gt;cologie2 since March 2010 and a close friend of Nicolas Hulot.
Biography
He started his career as an airline pilot at Air Alg&lt;U+00E9&gt;rie (1973&lt;U+2013&gt;1974) and moved to A&lt;U+00E9&gt;ropostale where he did night flights from 1974-1976. At Air France, he was a pilot on Sud Aviation Caravelle, Boeing 707 and 747 aircrafts, Captain (1989&lt;U+2013&gt;1992) then Captain Instructor (1992&lt;U+2013&gt;2004) on Airbus A310, A340 and A330.
In 1985, he applied for an Astronaut job at CNES and was one of ten finalists.
He became President of the A&lt;U+00E9&gt;ro-Club de France3 between 1995 and 2005. The centenary of the club took place during his presidency, and he organized a major exhibition of planes in Paris on the Champs-&lt;U+00C9&gt;lys&lt;U+00E9&gt;es to celebrate it.
Between 2005 and August 2010, G&lt;U+00E9&gt;rard Feldzer was head of the Mus&lt;U+00E9&gt;e de l'Air (French Air and Space Museum) at Le Bourget,.4 He made many animations and creations there including &quot;Planete Pilote&quot; (&quot;Planet pilot&quot;), the first space exhibition in the world aimed at 6-12 year olds.
He co-founded Zebunet (a micro-credit organisation for poor farmers in southern countries 5) in 2001 and he has been its Vice-President since then. He also founded the &quot;Les ailes de la ville&quot; scheme, which provides training and integration for young suburban people through repairing and constructing aircraft.6 As Founder and President of the &quot;Transports passion&quot; association, he has organized their annual meetings, exhibitions and events on ecomobility since 2005.7
On 1 January 2012, he became Officiers of the L&lt;U+00E9&gt;gion d'honneur8{{,}}.9
Media
Radio
Feldzer has had a weekly radio show on France Info since 2009. Recent episodes include Circulez! il y a le monde &lt;U+00E0&gt; voir (Move! there is the world to see)).10
TV series
Feldzer wrote and directed the following series:
Le Bar de l'escadrille (France 2, 1985)
Un ticket pour l'espace (France 2, 1990)
Les allum&lt;U+00E9&gt;s du sport (Canal+ 1992)
and co-wrote the transport series Transportez moi in 2011, which aired on LCP TV in 2012.
Books
Demain, je serai pilote.11
